        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(hooks): expose inbound reply metadata before dispatch",
        "body": "Fixes #88521.\n\n## Summary\n\n- carry inbound reply metadata through the canonical message hook context\n- expose `replyToId`, `replyToBody`, and `replyToSender` to `before_dispatch` event and context payloads\n- add coverage for the mapper and dispatch hook boundary\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Discord reply metadata was finalized into inbound context fields, but plugin `before_dispatch` hooks could not see the replied-to message id/body/sender and therefore could not implement reply-aware commands through the public hook API.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88521`, branch `fix/discord-reply-hook-context-88521`, commit `541db39710`.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/hooks/message-hook-mappers.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: The hook mapper and dispatch tests passed, and the outgoing commit author was verified:\n\n```text\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  14 passed (14)\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  188 passed (188)\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 22.17s\n541db39710 Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> Expose reply metadata to before_dispatch hooks\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: A finalized inbound context with `ReplyToId`, `ReplyToBody`, and `ReplyToSender` now reaches the canonical hook context and the `before_dispatch` event/context as `replyToId`, `replyToBody`, and `replyToSender`.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not connect to live Discord; this is covered at the finalized inbound-context to plugin-hook dispatch boundary.\n",
